    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">LOOP 语句</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The LOOP statement causes control to jump back to the beginning of the innermost <text styleclass="List">FOR, FOREACH , REPEAT or DO WHILE</text> statement.</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box">LOOP</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Remarks</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The LOOP statement is only valid within a DO WHILE, &#160;FOR ... NEXT, FOREACH .. NEXT or REPEAT .. UNTIL &#160;construct. A LOOP statement outside of either construct will raise a compile time error.</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">See Also<br/><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="command_DO_WHILE" styleclass="Body Text">DO WHILE </link><br/><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="command_FOR" styleclass="Body Text">FOR </link></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="command_FOREACH">FOREACH</link><br/><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="command_REPEAT_UNTIL">REPEAT UNTIL </link></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
  </body>
